# UInputNumber in catalog forms

Use shared presets and models from `app/utils/catalog-form.ts` (auto-imported). Do not duplicate `formatOptions` in components unless you first add or extend a preset there.

## Increment / decrement

`UInputNumber` shows increment and decrement controls by default. In this project, presets set `increment: false` and `decrement: false`.

- Keep those flags off unless the user explicitly asks for increment/decrement controls on that field.
- When they do ask, set `increment: true` and `decrement: true` only on that input (or on a dedicated preset), not globally.

## Format by field meaning

Bind the preset that matches the field semantics with `v-bind`:

| Meaning | Preset | Model helper |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Money (MXN) | `catalogCurrencyInputProps` | `useStringNumberModel` |
| Percentage | `catalogPercentInputProps` | `usePercentStringNumberModel` |
| Decimal factor / generic decimal | `catalogNumberInputProps` | `useStringNumberModel` |
| Integer ID / count | `catalogIntegerInputProps` | `useOptionalIntegerModel` or `useStringNumberModel` as needed |
| Coordinates | `catalogCoordinateInputProps` | `useStringNumberModel` with 6 decimals |
| Commission value by type | `catalogCommissionValueInputProps(commissionType)` | `useCommissionValueModel` |

For `commission_value`, remount or rebind when `commission_type` changes so currency vs percent formatting does not stick.

## API contract

Keep catalog payloads as strings unless the API type says otherwise. Formatting and percent scaling stay in the model helpers; do not change Zod schemas or detail mappers only to satisfy display.

```vue
<UInputNumber
  v-model="priceModel"
  v-bind="catalogCurrencyInputProps"
/>
```
